model_explanation: S1 asserts that Sue is the only person who received apples, but S2 introduces Rob as another recipient of apples, contradicting S1.
S2 repeats the fact that Rob received apples, which is consistent with S1's assertion that Rob (and only Rob) received apples.
S1 states that Bill was the only recipient of apples, and S2 that Mary did not receive any apples is consistent with that.
S1 says that only Mary received oranges, but S2 claims that Ellen also received oranges, which contradicts S1.
S1 says that Ellen was the sole recipient of apples, so it naturally follows that Tom didn't receive apples, which is consistent.
S1 limits the distribution of bananas to Rob, and S2 talks about oranges, a different fruit, so the two statements are about different facts and are independent.
if Bill only received bananas, as S1 states, then it follows that he did not receive grapes, which aligns with S2.
S1 says Ellen only got oranges, and S2 stating that Ellen did not receive grapes is in line with that, as oranges were the only thing given.
S1 asserts that Mary was the only recipient of bananas, so logically, no one else, like Ellen, received bananas, making S2 consistent.
S1 states Bill was the only one to get bananas, which means Tom did not receive any bananas, perfectly aligning with S2.
